Spokane.North Central High School (Spokane, Wash: North Central High School is a four-year public high school in Spokane, Washington, part of the Spokane Public Schools. It opened in 1908 as the second high school in the city; the original structure was razed and the new building opened in 1981. Enrollment during the 2006-07 school year was 1,610 in grades 9–12.
